{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"What does this product generate?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"It generates an 8-document Review-ready Section 8 notice and service file for England landlords: Form 3A Section 8 notice, N215 certificate of service, rent arrears schedule, service instructions, validity checklist, compliance declaration, case summary, and what-happens-next guide."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Why is the arrears schedule included?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Because a Section 8 rent arrears case is stronger when the arrears are set out clearly from the start. The schedule helps show how the debt built up and why the grounds are being relied on."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Does this help with Form 3A?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. Form 3A is the prescribed notice behind the current England Section 8 route, and this pack builds that official notice from your answers."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What if I also need the court paperwork?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Choose the Stage 2 Court & Possession Pack if you want the Section 8 notice, N5, N119, and the court-stage possession paperwork together in one flow."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can I preview the pack before I pay?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. You can preview the generated documents before purchase and regenerate them after edits if your facts or dates change."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Does this use court approved Section 8 documents?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. The pack uses the current official court-approved Form 3A notice format for England, with N215 certificate of service support, arrears schedule, service instructions, validity checklist, compliance declaration, case summary, and what-happens-next guide. You still need to complete and serve the documents correctly."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is this legally binding?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes - when completed and served correctly. This template follows post-May 2026 England rules, and the checklist helps you avoid common Section 8 notice mistakes."}}]}

