{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"What does the Stage 2 Court & Possession Pack include?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"It is the full Review-ready Section 8 court and possession file for England landlords. It includes everything in Stage 1 plus N5, N119, witness statement, court readiness status, court bundle index, evidence collection checklist, court filing guide, hearing checklist, eviction case summary, and arrears engagement letter."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Who is this built for?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"It is built for landlords in England who want both the notice/service stage and the court-stage possession paperwork prepared together."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"When should I choose this instead of the notice product?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Choose this pack when you want the court-possession paperwork as well as the Section 8 notice. If you only need to serve the notice first, the Stage 1 Notice & Service Pack is the better fit."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Does this include N5 and N119?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. The pack includes both forms because they are central to the court-stage possession claim for the current England route."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can I preview before I pay?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. You can review the generated pack before purchase and regenerate it later if the facts, dates, or evidence notes change."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Does this use court approved possession claim forms?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. The Complete Pack uses official court-approved possession forms where required, including N5 and N119, alongside Form 3A, N215, witness statement, evidence tools, and filing and hearing support. The court still decides the claim outcome from the completed forms and evidence."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is this legally binding?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes - when completed and filed correctly. This pack follows post-May 2026 England rules, and the checklist helps you avoid common possession claim mistakes."}}]}

