{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"What does the Money Claim Pack include?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"It includes the Letter Before Claim, reply and financial statement forms, Particulars of Claim, arrears schedule, interest calculation, the MCOL filing guide, and enforcement guidance for an England landlord claim."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can I claim for damage or cleaning after the tenant leaves?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. The pack can be used for rent arrears, damage, cleaning costs, bills, and other tenancy-related debts, provided you have evidence to support the figures."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can I combine rent arrears with damage claims?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. The workflow lets you build one claim file that covers multiple debt heads where that is appropriate."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can I claim interest on the debt?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. The pack includes an interest calculation so the claim value is worked out more clearly before the case is filed."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What happens after judgment if the tenant still does not pay?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"The enforcement guide explains the next-stage options such as bailiffs, attachment of earnings, and charging orders so the case does not stop at judgment."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is this a court approved money claim?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"No. Courts do not pre-approve any notice, claim form, or agreement. This Money Claim pack follows current England rules and includes checks to help you file correctly."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is this legally binding?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes - when completed and filed correctly. This pack follows post-May 2026 England rules, and the checklist helps you avoid common money claim mistakes."}}]}

