{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"What is the How to Rent guide?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"The How to Rent guide is a government document that landlords in England must provide to tenants at the start of an assured shorthold tenancy. It explains tenant rights and landlord responsibilities."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Do I have to give the How to Rent guide to my tenant?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes, if your property is in England and let on an assured private tenancy where the guide applies. It remains part of good compliance, even though Section 21 is no longer the live route for new England private-rented cases after 1 May 2026."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Where do I get the How to Rent guide?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Download the current version free from gov.uk. Search for \"How to rent\" or visit gov.uk/government/publications/how-to-rent. Always use the version current at the tenancy start date."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can I email the How to Rent guide?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes, but only if the tenant has agreed to receive documents by email. Keep evidence of the agreement and proof of sending (sent email with attachment). Alternatively, provide a hard copy."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Do I need to provide the How to Rent guide in Wales or Scotland?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"No. The How to Rent guide only applies in England. Wales and Scotland have different tenant information requirements under their respective housing laws."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What happens if I gave the wrong version of How to Rent?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Provide the current version promptly and keep evidence of service. For post-1 May 2026 England possession cases, focus on the current Form 3A / Section 8 route and make sure all compliance documents are in order before court action."}}]}

